# Screen 5.0.x passes the ANSI standout mode (smso/so and rmso/se) values
# (\E[3m and \E[37m) directly to the parent xterm instead of converting
# to xterm's values (\E[7m and # \E[27m). This causes text to be italicized
# instead of highlighted/inverse. So, we'll use screen.xterm-new by default.
# See: https://invisible-island.net/ncurses/terminfo.src.html#tic-screen
# See: https://invisible-island.net/ncurses/terminfo.src.html#tic-screen_xterm-new
# See: https://invisible-island.net/ncurses/terminfo.src.html#tic-xterm
# See: https://invisible-island.net/xterm/ctlseqs/ctlseqs.html#h4-Functions-using-CSI-_-ordered-by-the-final-character-lparen-s-rparen:CSI-Pm-m.1CA7
term screen.xterm-new

